=== Code Patterns ===

// [Pattern] Keep generator-dependent calculations inside the comprehension or pass the generator variable explicitly
// Intent: Avoid scope errors when a comprehension element needs a derived value based on the generator variable.
// Template:
xs = [ elem i | i <- idxs ]
  where
    elem i = ... i ...
// Example:
coeffs = [ coeff i | i <- [0 .. 255] ]
  where
    coeff i = bits @ (base i)

// [Pattern] Drive sequence reshaping with an explicit result type for `split`
// Intent: When one input sequence can be partitioned in multiple ways, fix the intended structure by annotating the result type.
// Template:
<name> xs = ys
  where
    ys : [parts][each]<elem_type>
    ys = split xs
// Example:
msg' : [diameter][row][8]
msg' = split msg

// [Pattern] Use `foldl` when only the final accumulator matters
// Intent: Collapse a finite sequence to one value when intermediate running states are not needed as first-class output.
// Template:
result = foldl step init xs
// Example:
evalPoly p x = foldl (+) zero terms

// [Pattern] Use backtick notation to turn numeric type parameters into values
// Intent: Reference a numeric type parameter as a term-level number inside expressions.
// Template:
f : {n, a, b} (fin n, Literal n b) => [n]a -> b
f _ = `n
// Example:
length : {n, a, b} (fin n, Literal n b) => [n]a -> b
length _ = `n

// [Pattern] Use value-level recursion when an iteration count is computed from values
// Intent: Translate loops whose counts come from values by explicit recursion over a runtime counter or index.
// Template:
go i state =
  if i == stop then state
  else go (i + 1) state'
    where
      state' = ... i ... state
// Example:
butterflyLoop j state =
  if j == end then state
  else butterflyLoop (j + 1) state'
    where
      state' = step j state


